  "title": "Continue to show a selected refinement when it's over maxValuesPerFacet",
  "body": "This issue is  directly linked to http://stackoverflow.com/questions/36319673/algolia-instantsearch-refinementlist-item-toogle-when-search-for-something-else .\nThe user want to be able to keep track of already selected refinements in his refinement list, even when its count would imply it's not sent back as a facet value in the response.\n\nHere the refinement is selected:\n![selected](http://i.stack.imgur.com/uUbhu.png)\n\nBut if your change the query, it disappears:\n![selected but gone](http://i.stack.imgur.com/6SfZ4.png)\n\nAs I've said in the answer, this is partly solved by _currentRefinedValues_. Do we want to also expose an option on faceting widgets?\n",
